<item>
            <title>[LU-870] Console message: &quot;is it ok to have flags 0x420 and 0x5a8 in the same brw?&quot;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-870</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We are seeing frequent messages like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nov 21 12:20:58 hype352 kernel: LustreError: 7689:0:(osc_request.c:1229:can_merge_pages()) is it ok to have flags 0x420 and 0x5a8 in the same brw?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;on the console of 2.1 lustre clients.  That is a pretty terrible console message.  One way or another we need to eliminate it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If it is a problem, we need to fix whatever is going one.  If there is no problem, the message needs to be removed from the console.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>2.1.0-12chaos, &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/chaos/lustre&quot;&gt;https://github.com/chaos/lustre&lt;/a&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12509">LU-870</key>
