                            <comment id="23269" author="adilger" created="Mon, 21 Nov 2011 18:18:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this as a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-651&quot; title=&quot;Strange error message &amp;quot;is it ok to have flags 0x... and 0x... in the same brw?&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-651&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-651&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  It looks like the referenced patch is not the correct way to resolve this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23268" author="adilger" created="Mon, 21 Nov 2011 18:15:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The flags that are different appear to be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;0x100 = OBD_BRW_NOQUOTA&lt;br/&gt;
0x080 = OBD_BRW_NOCACHE&lt;br/&gt;
0x008 = OBD_BRW_SYNC&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There was a patch recently merged to master to address OBD_BRW_NOQUOTA issue from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-651&quot; title=&quot;Strange error message &amp;quot;is it ok to have flags 0x... and 0x... in the same brw?&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-651&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-651&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/1328&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/1328&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The other flags are already excluded in 2.1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
